<H1 Style="color: RED;">NATIONAL SERVICE TRAINING PROGRAM (NSTP CWTS)</h1>
<h1 style="color: blue;">BASIC PRINCIPLES IN WATER SEARCH AND RESCUE</h1>
<b> WASAR </b>
<p> To search and rescue in the sea, rivers, lakes, in regions, and fields that are experiencing floods, and in general, wherever water is a hazard to human life</p>
<b> WASAR TRAINING</b>
<p> The training aims to enhance the skills in basic life support, standard first aid, different water swimming techniques,
water safety, life saving rescue techniques, survival techniques and mass casualty incident operations.</p>
<p>Basic Water Rescue Training provides individuals with the knowledge and skills necessary to prevent, recognize, and respond to many types of aquatic emergencies.</p>
<hr> TOP 4 PRIORITIES</hr>
<ul>
<li>Personal safety </li>
<li>Companion/ Teammate </li>
<li>Community/Public </li>
<li>Victim</li>
</ul>
